description:
&lt;p&gt;With COVID-19 continuing to play a major part in all our everyday lives, we are expanding our capacity over the winter period and need your support to help deliver excellent care to our patients. We can offer ad-hoc shifts and/or longer-term placements through our Staff Bank, to work around your commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you a qualified phlebotomist ?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’ve answered &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;‘yes’&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, we’d love to talk to you about joining our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust (CLCH) works across ten London boroughs and Hertfordshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We currently have Band 3 Community phlebotomy vacancies across London: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Central London Community Healthcare NHS Trust (CLCH), community healthcare is our focus and our passion. We champion the role of community health professionals to make sure our patients get great care closer to home and we have recently been rated &lt;em&gt;Good&lt;/em&gt; by the Care Quality Commission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We believe community nursing gives dedicated healthcare professionals the opportunity to spend more time with the patients you care for in their own environment and work collaboratively with other clinicians to provide more coordinated care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our temporary staffing shifts are calculated hourly and paid weekly. You are paid only for the hours you actually work during any Assignment. Bank workers are paid on fixed third point based on the Agenda for Change (AFC) pay bands.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HCAS: Inner 20% - Outer 15% - Fringe 5% (As per AfC)&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
